             <p></p><h3><b><u>Euler's totient function</u></b></h3><p></p>
              <h4>
                <p>Euler's totient function, denoted by, =CF=95(n),=20
                is a mathematical function that counts the number of positi=
ve=20
                integers less than or equal to n and also are coprime to=20
                n. In other words, =CF=95(n) gives the count of integers be=
tween 1 and n=20
                inclusive, that do not share any common factors with n othe=
r than 1.</p>
                Euler's totient function has various applications in number=
 theory=20
                and cryptography, particularly in the RSA encryption algori=
thm.=20

